Key Learning Points
IDOR is one of the most common Broken Access Control vulnerabilities.
Changing a user identifier should never grant access to another user's resources.
Authentication alone is not enough; authorization must also be enforced.
Every request that accesses a resource must verify ownership.
Horizontal privilege escalation occurs when a user accesses another user's data.
Pentester's Perspective
Whenever you encounter parameters such as:

id=
user=
userid=
username=
account=
customer=
profile=
order=
invoice=
document=
file=
download=
api=
always ask:

Can I modify this value?
Does the server verify ownership?
Do I receive another user's data?
Can I access resources that belong to someone else?
IDOR vulnerabilities are among the easiest to test and one of the most valuable findings in bug bounty programs and penetration tests.

